{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/50°C\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt again <b>20 sec\/50°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add reserved ground almonds and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Add icing sugar and flour then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add egg whites then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and place in fridge to chill for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C.","Generously grease 8 individual tartlet tins Ø 10 cm and line the base of each with baking paper.","Spoon chilled mixture into tart tins and distribute raspberries between them. Place tins on a baking tray and bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C) or until golden brown at the edges. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["170 g blanched almonds","120 g unsalted butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","270 g icing sugar","65 g plain flour","5 egg whites, from large eggs","300 g frozen raspberries"]}],"id":"r247617","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-uY9MNUp50gQ\/XZWeXo5M5bI\/AAAAAAAAey8\/tih2zOnQJbE3PNNPRHKJ2RjYq1kAWjqOwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Y9sTjiwDxirTq1Rw.png","title":"Raspberry Tartlets","publishedAt":"2018-02-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11.5 g","fat":"34 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"57.5 g","calories":"2502 kJ \/ 599 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, baking tray, loose-based tartlet tins (Ø 10 cm), refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["These simple yet sophisticated tartlets are a great way of using up egg whites you may have leftover from making other recipes."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}